7.  Manuscript Editor (international, 1.5 person-months, intermittent) 

7.  The manuscript editor will edit the Key Indicators 2011 special chapter and assist in 
preparing  the  highlights  of  Key  indicators  2011,  tables  and  charts,  and  the  presentation 
materials. In particular, the manuscript editor will: 

(i)  reorganize text so subject matter is easy to understand and is logically presented; 
(ii)  eliminate wordiness and repetition, and reduce ambiguity; 
(iii)  query discrepancies, possible typographic errors, non-English terms, obvious errors 
in mathematical calculations, questionable proper names, bibliographic references, 
and the like, but excluding fact checking; 
(iv)  edit the foreword and acknowledgements, reference lists, notes and footnotes, and 
tables and figures, and recast these if required; 
(v)  ensure that the text conforms to ADB’s Handbook of Style and Usage; 
(vi)  check references to tables, figures, appendixes, and other parts of the text; 
(vii)  work closely with the author and check the author’s final changes;  
(viii)  check and sign off on the layout; and 
(ix)  work with the copyeditor assigned to the statistical tables to ensure that a consistent 
style is used in all parts of the publication. 

8.  Economics  and  Statistics  Specialists  (national,  54.0  person-months,  9 
consultants) 

8.  The consultants should have a background in economics or statistics and experience 
working with social, economic, and financial statistics, preferably official statistics. They should 
also be able to work very well with Microsoft Excel. In particular, the consultants will: 

(i)  generate updated Key Indicators questionnaires for the assigned regional members 
of ADB; 
(ii)  follow up the updated replies to questionnaires with the statistical contacts; 
(iii)  validate  data  in  the  replies  according  to  the  guidelines  and  seek  necessary 
clarifications from the statistical contacts to ensure completeness and correctness of 
the most updated country data; 
(iv)  finalize assigned country tables by pooling validated data from the replies and data 
from  relevant  international  data  sources,  and  ensure  the  consistency  and 
correctness of all data points;  
(v)  update and generate country, regional, and MDG tables; 
(vi)  update the Statistical Database System using the latest data in the country, MDG, 
and regional tables; 
(vii)  review the statistical commentaries for the regional and MDG tables to ensure that 
the analysis is consistent with the data in the tables and with other ADB publications; 
(viii)  assist in other activities in the preparation of various parts of Key Indicators 2011; 
and 
(ix)  perform other related technical and administrative tasks assigned.
